23:14.727 --> 23:17.830
in our company, Candi.

23:17.830 --> 23:19.331
Sharks, imagine this.

23:19.331 --> 23:21.300
Think back
to when you were a kid.

23:21.300 --> 23:24.069
Think about your favorite
celebrity or athlete

23:24.069 --> 23:25.504
that you always
wanted to meet.

23:25.504 --> 23:27.139
Now, imagine
if you had the chance

23:27.139 --> 23:28.374
to actually meet
that person.

23:28.374 --> 23:30.142
Maybe it's a movie star.

23:30.142 --> 23:33.712
Maybe it's a 5'5"
comedic rock star.

23:33.712 --> 23:35.114
Who knows?

23:35.114 --> 23:37.516
But imagine if you had a chance
to actually talk to that person.

23:37.516 --> 23:39.919
I'm not talking about
an impersonal video

23:39.919 --> 23:42.621
where the celebrity really
doesn't know who you are.

23:42.621 --> 23:44.690
I'm talking about the chance
to really interact

23:44.690 --> 23:45.758
with that person.

23:45.758 --> 23:47.092
Sounds like a dream, right?

23:47.092 --> 23:50.963
Well, at Candi,
we're making dreams come true

23:50.963 --> 23:54.633
with one memorable
meet and greet at a time.

23:54.633 --> 23:58.037
Candi is a social network
that allows fans to video chat

23:58.037 --> 24:00.139
with their favorite celebrities
and influencers.

24:00.139 --> 24:02.207
But don't just take
our word for it.

24:02.207 --> 24:07.112
Take the word of Grammy
Award‐winning artist Mya.

24:07.112 --> 24:10.449
<i>Hey, Keithan. Hey, Quiante.</i>
<i>It's Mya here.</i>

24:10.449 --> 24:12.651
<i>You look amazing in that dress,</i>
<i>by the way.</i>

24:12.651 --> 24:14.053
<i>And hello, Sharks.</i>

24:14.053 --> 24:16.922
<i>It's such a pleasure</i>
<i>to be in the Tank with you.</i>

24:16.922 --> 24:20.025
<i>I love being on Candi so I can</i>
<i>chat with fans just like you,</i>

24:20.025 --> 24:23.162
<i>and I hope that you give them</i>
<i>a great deal.</i>

24:23.162 --> 24:27.099
<i>Much love, everyone.</i>
<i>Peace and blessings.</i>

24:27.099 --> 24:28.200
So Sharks...

24:28.200 --> 24:29.802
Both: ...which one of you
wants to walk

24:29.802 --> 24:32.304
the red carpet with Candi?

24:32.304 --> 24:35.774
So is this a business that
you already have up and running?

24:35.774 --> 24:38.644
Yes, so we launched
in April of 2020.

24:38.644 --> 24:42.247
Since launching,
we've made about over $100,000.

24:42.247 --> 24:43.582
What's the business model?

24:43.582 --> 24:45.751
Let's say I want to talk
to Kevin Hart. What happens?

24:45.751 --> 24:47.052
Yeah, absolutely.

24:47.052 --> 24:49.021
So each celebrity sets
their rate for a five‐minute

24:49.021 --> 24:50.255
virtual meet and greet.

24:50.255 --> 24:53.425
Of that rate, they keep 75%.
We earn 25%.

24:53.425 --> 24:54.660
How it works
is you come to our website,

24:54.660 --> 24:56.528
you find Kevin's profile,

24:56.528 --> 24:59.031
you suggest the time that you
would like to meet with him.

24:59.031 --> 25:01.033
Our team coordinates
to try to make that happen.

25:01.033 --> 25:03.068
Does Kevin set his price?
Yes.

25:03.068 --> 25:04.803
Each celebrity
sets their own rate,

25:04.803 --> 25:06.338
but obviously,
we consult with them.

25:06.338 --> 25:08.307
What's the lowest
and highest price?

25:08.307 --> 25:09.708
Yeah, we have celebrities,

25:09.708 --> 25:12.378
TikTok influencers as low as,
you know, 5 or 10 bucks,

25:12.378 --> 25:14.613
and we have Chaka Khan
is 400 bucks.

25:14.613 --> 25:17.950
What's the engagement that
you've had with your customers,

25:17.950 --> 25:19.952
and how big
is the platform?

25:19.952 --> 25:23.455
Absolutely. So we have over
350 celebrities and influencers.

25:23.455 --> 25:26.191
To date, we've done over
2,000 meet and greets.

25:26.191 --> 25:29.395
40% of our fans have used
our service at least four times.

25:29.395 --> 25:31.030
Where are these fans
coming from?

25:31.030 --> 25:33.098
We don't do any traditional
forms of marketing.

25:33.098 --> 25:34.767
Right now, we get our customers
from our celebrities

25:34.767 --> 25:37.136
posting on their social media
and through outreach.

25:37.136 --> 25:38.270
So you're using
the platform

25:38.270 --> 25:40.105
of the celebrities
that you guys have

25:40.105 --> 25:43.042
in hopes that you'll get
a return in engagement

25:43.042 --> 25:44.443
from their fans
to come over to Candi?

25:44.443 --> 25:45.544
‐Absolutely.
‐As of now, yes.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.279
So Candi doesn't necessarily
have an engine

25:47.279 --> 25:50.049
that they've built that you guys
are using to distribute from?

25:50.049 --> 25:52.551
Well, we would say the engine is
the celebrities, right ‐‐

25:52.551 --> 25:55.354
That you posting, obviously,
to your fan base.

25:55.354 --> 25:57.623
You'd be a billionaire
if he posted once.

25:57.623 --> 25:59.725
Yeah, exactly, right?
That's the idea.

25:59.725 --> 26:00.993
So tell us about you.

26:00.993 --> 26:02.561
We were really like
a cliché couple.

26:02.561 --> 26:04.329
I was the captain
of a cheerleading team.

26:04.329 --> 26:06.165
He was the captain
of the football team.

26:06.165 --> 26:07.666
Following high school,

26:07.666 --> 26:10.169
I attended
the University of Illinois,

26:10.169 --> 26:13.672
where I graduated
within three years with honors.
Wow.

26:13.672 --> 26:16.742
And we actually had
our first son, Scotty,

26:16.742 --> 26:18.310
my last year
of undergrad,

26:18.310 --> 26:20.312
so that was definitely
difficult.

26:20.312 --> 26:23.482
When we launched Candi
of April of 2020,

26:23.482 --> 26:26.018
I was four months' pregnant
with our second son, Chase.

26:26.018 --> 26:28.420
His birthday is today.
[ Laughs ]

26:28.420 --> 26:30.656
And up until labor
and delivery,

26:30.656 --> 26:32.124
I was still working,

26:32.124 --> 26:34.526
and the next day
after I delivered Chase...
Of course.

26:34.526 --> 26:35.828
...I had to work
a meet and greet,

26:35.828 --> 26:38.597
and I had my baby on my boob
and my laptop on my knees,

26:38.597 --> 26:40.132
so I've been grinding
ever since.

26:40.132 --> 26:43.068
We like to say we don't really
have maternity policy at Candi.

26:43.068 --> 26:44.503
What's your background?

26:44.503 --> 26:47.206
So, unfortunately, I was born to
a mother who abandoned me

26:47.206 --> 26:50.175
and my two younger brothers
when I was just 4 years old.

26:50.175 --> 26:52.744
Fast forward a little bit,
I get to college,

26:52.744 --> 26:54.847
I had an opportunity to play
Division I college football

26:54.847 --> 26:56.548
at Eastern
Illinois University.

26:56.548 --> 26:58.117
I'm having the best time
in my life,

26:58.117 --> 27:00.619
but I was unhappy because I knew
what my younger brothers

27:00.619 --> 27:02.254
were facing
on a day to day basis.

27:02.254 --> 27:04.356
And so after my freshman year,
I was 19 years old.

27:04.356 --> 27:07.392
I went back and I adopted
my 14‐ and 15‐year‐old brothers,

27:07.392 --> 27:08.327
legally becoming
their father.

27:08.327 --> 27:09.128
‐That's so nice.
‐Mm!

27:09.128 --> 27:10.295
So I was a full‐time

27:10.295 --> 27:11.830
Division I
college athlete.

27:11.830 --> 27:13.699
I was a single father
of two teenage boys,

27:13.699 --> 27:15.834
and I also graduated undergrad
in three years,

27:15.834 --> 27:17.402
with my bachelor's
of applied engineering.

27:17.402 --> 27:19.538
So in our house, if you
graduate with a bachelor's

27:19.538 --> 27:21.440
in more than three years,
you're probably slouching.

27:21.440 --> 27:23.175
[ Laughter ]

27:23.175 --> 27:25.077
Then I had the opportunity
to go to law school

27:25.077 --> 27:26.445
at the University of Illinois
College of Law.

27:26.445 --> 27:28.747
I graduated in three years
with honors.
Yeah!

27:28.747 --> 27:32.217
And for the past six years,
I've been practicing mergers,
acquisitions, representing

27:32.217 --> 27:33.652
some of the biggest numbers
in the world.
Fabulous.

27:33.652 --> 27:35.220
How did you
think of the idea?

27:35.220 --> 27:36.255
Yeah, absolutely.

27:36.255 --> 27:37.523
We saw
some reaction videos

27:37.523 --> 27:39.458
from some competitors
in the industry,

27:39.458 --> 27:41.326
and we saw how excited
fans were,

27:41.326 --> 27:42.861
and happy
and crying and elated.

27:42.861 --> 27:44.763
And we said,
how amazing would it be,

27:44.763 --> 27:46.198
instead of someone
giving you the phone

27:46.198 --> 27:47.499
and saying,
"Press play,"

27:47.499 --> 27:48.967
they gave you the phone
and Barbara was actually there

27:48.967 --> 27:50.502
to have a conversation
with you?

27:50.502 --> 27:52.671
How much more personal
that experience would be.

27:52.671 --> 27:54.506
The first thing to understand
is this ‐‐

27:54.506 --> 27:56.508
We have no experience
in Hollywood,

27:56.508 --> 27:58.076
no connections.

27:58.076 --> 28:00.979
I'm not a manager, she's not
an agent, no connection.
Good for you.

28:00.979 --> 28:02.948
We were everyday people
sitting on our couch.

28:02.948 --> 28:07.853
In the first week from us
having an idea of really trying
to push Candi to being live,

28:07.853 --> 28:10.889
we got 26 influencers
and celebrities in one week.

28:10.889 --> 28:12.157
How we do that is hustle.

28:12.157 --> 28:14.226
You guys are asking
for $500,000.

28:14.226 --> 28:15.160
What are you gonna do
with the money?

28:15.160 --> 28:16.762
So, we want to do
three things.

28:16.762 --> 28:19.665
Most importantly, we want to
have better technology.

28:19.665 --> 28:21.433
Yes, we do want an app.

28:21.433 --> 28:22.901
And two,
we want to hire more team

28:22.901 --> 28:24.570
for our talent acquisition

28:24.570 --> 28:27.139
so we can hone in
on more quality talent.

28:27.139 --> 28:29.374
And lastly, we want to increase
our marketing efforts.

28:29.374 --> 28:31.710
So, you really need an app,
because it's very hard

28:31.710 --> 28:35.480
to get people and acquire
customers and fans...
Yes.

28:35.480 --> 28:36.648
...I mean,
just out on the web.

28:36.648 --> 28:38.517
Hart: I think
what's even harder is,

28:38.517 --> 28:40.452
you know,
the talent pool, right?

28:40.452 --> 28:42.921
The talent pool is going
to guarantee you a return,

28:42.921 --> 28:44.389
which is where
I'm having trouble,

28:44.389 --> 28:47.392
because, you know, these things
have existed before.

28:47.392 --> 28:49.895
And the reason why they come
far, few, and in between

28:49.895 --> 28:52.698
in a place of success
is because they fall apart

28:52.698 --> 28:56.969
based on not being able to stay
true to what the commitment was.

28:56.969 --> 28:59.338
And I just don't know
if there's a world

28:59.338 --> 29:01.740
where you can guarantee
that type of talent.

29:01.740 --> 29:04.009
Cuban: Yeah, no one's saying
it's a bad business for them.
It's not.

29:04.009 --> 29:06.478
Right? Look,
if you're doing $100,000

29:06.478 --> 29:08.880
and you're netting $25,000,
right,

29:08.880 --> 29:10.415
and you're working from home,

29:10.415 --> 29:12.684
that's not a bad business,
but that's a different question

29:12.684 --> 29:15.020
than whether or not
it's an investable business.
That's the big side.

29:15.020 --> 29:17.889
And if I can interject,
I think it is, right?

29:17.889 --> 29:19.424
I heard you say before,
Mr. Wonderful,

29:19.424 --> 29:20.792
you're looking for
a great business model

29:20.792 --> 29:22.427
that you can
pour gasoline on.
Right.

29:22.427 --> 29:24.296
If you look at what we've been
able to do with no experience

29:24.296 --> 29:26.732
in the industry,
no relationships, with no ties,

29:26.732 --> 29:27.966
you pour a little gasoline
on that,

29:27.966 --> 29:29.101
you're going to
have a huge fire.

29:29.101 --> 29:31.169
Yeah, but you asked for
a lot of gasoline.

29:31.169 --> 29:34.239
Honestly, I‐I love the attempt,
and I love the effort.

29:34.239 --> 29:39.278
I just think it's too early to
attach myself or get involved,

29:39.278 --> 29:40.846
even from an investment
perspective,

29:40.846 --> 29:43.048
because we don't really know

29:43.048 --> 29:44.750
if this is something
that not only works,

29:44.750 --> 29:47.519
but who's to say that
somebody won't swoop in

29:47.519 --> 29:49.821
and do the bigger
version of Candi, right?

29:49.821 --> 29:51.790
Well, guess what, Kevin?
That can be us.

29:51.790 --> 29:53.725
We just need
your validation, right?

29:53.725 --> 29:55.494
We need the fact that
Kevin Hart has said

29:55.494 --> 29:58.263
he puts his name
and his stamp on that.
Life's not that way.

29:58.263 --> 30:01.933
You don't get some golden bullet
that just builds a business.
Fair.

30:01.933 --> 30:03.835
It just doesn't happen
that way.

30:03.835 --> 30:05.237
That was a big problem,
when you said,

30:05.237 --> 30:08.440
"Well, you know, we're going
to use our celebrities,

30:08.440 --> 30:10.175
and then from them,
in hopes

30:10.175 --> 30:12.878
get people to come on
and X, Y, and Z."

30:12.878 --> 30:14.313
It's a trickle effect.

30:14.313 --> 30:16.948
You don't have an engine
right now that you're saying,

30:16.948 --> 30:19.318
we know for sure
we have 10,000 people

30:19.318 --> 30:21.520
that we're accessing
and that we're beating up

30:21.520 --> 30:22.921
and that we want
to start with,

30:22.921 --> 30:24.856
and in hopes with these
10,000 people,

30:24.856 --> 30:26.925
well, we want to
grow some awareness in Candi.

30:26.925 --> 30:30.962
It was all based on the talent
that you <i>hope</i> to get.

30:30.962 --> 30:33.632
I think you guys came in
extremely aggressive

30:33.632 --> 30:36.735
with the number,
and the business model,

30:36.735 --> 30:38.437
it just didn't
match the ask.

30:38.437 --> 30:40.772
So it's honestly
too early for me.

30:40.772 --> 30:43.342
I have to say it.
I'm out.

30:43.342 --> 30:45.577
You made a fundamental
"Shark Tank" mistake.

30:45.577 --> 30:47.612
You asked for 500K, right?

30:47.612 --> 30:51.249
And you only gave up 15%,
and you're expecting us

30:51.249 --> 30:54.019
to be that door opener
all the time.

30:54.019 --> 30:56.521
That's a lot of work.
That's a lot of obligation.

30:56.521 --> 30:58.190
And so the numbers
don't make sense to me.

30:58.190 --> 30:59.791
So for that reason,
I'm out.

30:59.791 --> 31:02.060
♪♪

31:02.060 --> 31:05.330
I'm curious as to see,
like, what what
numbers are investable?

31:05.330 --> 31:07.999
if this was $50,000
and a flier, maybe.

31:07.999 --> 31:11.403
But it's $500,000.
It's too much gasoline for me.

31:11.403 --> 31:13.271
I'm out.

31:13.271 --> 31:15.640
You're a walking
billboard of inspiration

31:15.640 --> 31:17.142
for anybody who would listen.
100%.

31:17.142 --> 31:18.677
But the ask is just too much.

31:18.677 --> 31:20.312
And like the other Sharks,

31:20.312 --> 31:21.613
that's the reason
I'm out, as well.

31:21.613 --> 31:23.348
I'm out.
Thank you.
I appreciate that.

31:23.348 --> 31:24.449
Thank you
for your time.

31:24.449 --> 31:25.884
‐Lori?
‐Lori?

31:25.884 --> 31:29.321
What happened is, is your ask
was much higher

31:29.321 --> 31:31.823
than what you've actually sold.
Absolutely.

31:31.823 --> 31:33.992
And I'm not confident
that you're going to be able

31:33.992 --> 31:35.660
to grow it that big,
that fast,

31:35.660 --> 31:38.697
with all the competition
that's out there already.

31:38.697 --> 31:41.900
I'm so sorry, but I'm out.

31:41.900 --> 31:44.069
Keithan, you guys are smart.
You will figure it out.

31:44.069 --> 31:45.604
‐And we are.
‐Thank you, guys.

31:45.604 --> 31:48.273
‐Thank you.
‐Thank you. Have a good one.

31:48.273 --> 31:51.243
♪♪

31:51.243 --> 31:55.580
We do regret the amount of
the ask, but it was great
just meeting Kevin Hart.

31:55.580 --> 31:56.848
I mean, any time you have
a guest Shark like that

31:56.848 --> 31:59.684
that can give you
such invaluable advice,

31:59.684 --> 32:01.153
you know, I feel like
we got a free

32:01.153 --> 32:03.155
consulting session, right?
Mm‐hmm.

32:03.155 --> 32:04.923
Really, is how I feel.

32:04.923 --> 32:07.526
I'm way too familiar
with that space,

32:07.526 --> 32:11.763
and a lot of mistakes early on
in my business career

32:11.763 --> 32:13.098
were made in that space.

32:13.098 --> 32:14.566
‐Oh, really?
‐Oh, yeah.

32:14.566 --> 32:17.369
All based off of, "Oh, said
person has this many followers.

32:17.369 --> 32:20.205
If we get them to do this, then
this is going to be a success."

32:20.205 --> 32:21.406
And that's not true.

32:21.406 --> 32:22.674
Can have high numbers,

32:22.674 --> 32:25.110
but what's important
is high engagement.
Exactly.

32:25.110 --> 32:29.681
♪♪

32:32.417 --> 32:37.155
♪♪

32:37.155 --> 32:39.357
Narrator: Next up is
an entertainment company

32:39.357 --> 32:42.127
with representation
as a mission.

32:42.127 --> 32:49.034
♪♪

32:49.034 --> 32:50.969
Hi, Sharks. I'm Manuel.

32:50.969 --> 32:53.405
‐And I'm Geiszel.
‐And I'm Teunis.

32:53.405 --> 32:55.941
And we are Black Sands
Entertainment.

32:55.941 --> 32:59.778
We're currently seeking
$500,000 for 5% of our company.
[ Laughs ]

32:59.778 --> 33:02.681
Sharks,
America loves entertainment,

33:02.681 --> 33:05.884
be it movies,
television, anime, or comics.

33:05.884 --> 33:08.520
There has never been more
content than there is today.

33:08.520 --> 33:12.057
But there is still a struggle
to find content and characters

33:12.057 --> 33:14.092
that represent
the Black community's

33:14.092 --> 33:16.862
historical achievements
before slavery.

33:16.862 --> 33:21.199
That's why we created
Black Sands Entertainment.

33:21.199 --> 33:23.235
Black Sands is one of
the only successful

33:23.235 --> 33:25.337
Black‐owned
publishing houses in America,

33:25.337 --> 33:27.138
and it all started
with the flagship title

33:27.138 --> 33:28.673
"Black Sands
the Seven Kingdoms."

33:28.673 --> 33:31.409
And after 100,000 copies sold,

33:31.409 --> 33:33.945
we knew a legend had been born.
‐Wow.

33:33.945 --> 33:36.581
Our sales are phenomenal.

33:36.581 --> 33:40.785
But one thing that can take
a $1 million publishing IP

33:40.785 --> 33:43.021
and turn it into
a $1 billion licensing

33:43.021 --> 33:44.623
and merchandising IP

33:44.623 --> 33:46.725
is to make it
into an animated series.

33:46.725 --> 33:49.361
We are here to give Black
and brown creators

33:49.361 --> 33:53.198
a place to tell their stories
and shine a spotlight

33:53.198 --> 33:55.467
on the rich history
of our people.

33:55.467 --> 33:56.668
So Sharks...

33:56.668 --> 33:59.070
All: Who is ready
to join the Black Sands family?

33:59.070 --> 34:00.972
Ooh! Okay.

34:00.972 --> 34:02.574
Please sit back, relax.

34:02.574 --> 34:03.909
We're going to give you
a little taste of the future

34:03.909 --> 34:06.344
of Black Sands Entertainment.

34:06.344 --> 34:08.380
Man:
How long has he trained you?

34:08.380 --> 34:10.248
Man #2:
I did not train him.

34:10.248 --> 34:13.785
I took him into the wilderness
for five years.

34:13.785 --> 34:17.155
He has survived.

34:17.155 --> 34:18.657
I forbid this battle!

34:18.657 --> 34:21.493
You will stop nothing.
Damn it, brother!

34:21.493 --> 34:25.597
Why must you be like this
all the time?

34:25.597 --> 34:28.300
Man #3: Ausar,
you need to think this through.

34:28.300 --> 34:32.037
Ausar: There is nothing
to think about.

34:32.037 --> 34:34.673
♪♪

34:34.673 --> 34:36.741
Blacks Sands.
You can read it and watch it.

34:36.741 --> 34:38.143
Now let's go.

34:38.143 --> 34:39.711
All right. Well, you know what?
I'm gonna start here.

34:39.711 --> 34:41.680
And not just because I'm Black,

34:41.680 --> 34:44.983
but because I understand
the value behind IP,

34:44.983 --> 34:47.185
the want and
need for it.

34:47.185 --> 34:49.120
What's the cost that you put
